rComments: By far my most enjoyable class. Reibetanz is extremely passionate about her work, and this in turn rubs off on all of her students within the lecture. The content is rich, though she will never leave a topic unclear. I could sit and listen to her recite poetry all day; she's witty and inspirational. Would definitely recommend.

I was personally so excited for this course but her attitude and   boring lectures definetly killed my passion for poetry. She doesnt post anything on line, can be quiet snappy and just constantly reads from the books. Although  incredibly knowledgeable, she made the class very uninspiring.

Honestly she made a class which could have been interesting inaccessible and boring. Her class was unpleasant and had I been aware of her teaching style I would have made a conscious effort to avoid her section. She seems like a nice lady but the class was just not up to the same standard as other english classes at U of T

Reibetanz is one of the best professors I've ever had at U of T. She is a real, honest-to-God professor. She knows her stuff, is sharp, and will call out any dumbass opinion, so always make sure you're ready before you speak. On the other hand, she's not a jerk; she really cares about the material and is helpful if you have questions.
Exceptional prof, engaging, informative and inspirational. A wealth of knowledge.
I didn't mind her.  I found her quite approachable.  Although, her lectures were uninspiring.  She sat the entire time and read from the text. She did get grumpy over some questions asked.
She does not offer any help whatsoever, the TAs emails are not given to us for further instruction. She is so outdated she does not post anything online. She is the worst teacher I have ever had!!
Yay! Reibetanz

Prof. Reibetanz should not be teaching. She's obviously more interested in the day to day operations of the department and her personal research. She makes her distaste for students abundantly clear, and her willingness to help them reflects this. Curt, with little compassion for students, Julia Reibetanz is one of the worst instructors I've ever h

Professor Reibetanz is warm, funny, and a delight to have even at 9am. I had a passion for poetry before I took her course, but little skill when it came to understanding its subtleties. She is an incredible close reader, a joy to listen to, and the most influential prof I have ever had-- I doubt I would have succeeded as much as I have without her

Prof speaks so quietly that she cannot be heard at the back of the room. She can be crabby when  discussions or questions do not go the direction she desires. She does not make the material come to life. However she is not a difficult marker.

Great prof! Very passionate about poetry, and definitely draws the true message in poems that at first, didnt make sense to me at all.  She is also very kind outside class and a fair marker. Her wisdom can be sensed when she lectures, and makes you think of literature not just as a subject but as a mirror, where you can look into your life. :)

Comments like "Great Course, Great Prof." tend to make me believe that some professors' kids log on to this site to praise their parents. I don't understand her methods. No clear in any way. Is she mean-spirited and vindictive? That's just a question.
Lectures are rambling, not much focus.  Voice fades off at the end of sentences.  Can be unexpectedly crabby in personal meetings. Managed interesting discussions in class, though.

Not friendly?  SO friendly, the friendliest  I've had!!  Passionate about the material, encouraging when you comment in class or write a good paper.  Yes, she's quiet, so don't sit in the back.  A clear and animated lecture style.  No groupwork, quizzes, or silly things like that.  LOTS of readings, esp. in the beginning.
great prof. great course.
What class was the previous rater writing about. This class brought out the sleeper in me. You could hear me snore from Convocation Hall. You'd have to sit at her feet to hear her. Too easy.

I love her. She's extremely intelligent, helpful, and passionate about her work. I especially love it when she reads to the class -- her expression is impeccable! She's a little quiet, though, so sit up close. She made my English experience a pleasant one -- she doesn't make you over-analyze purposely subjective texts, for example.

At first she struck me as unapproachable and sour. However, she is extremely friendly and is very enthusiastic about the material. She also has a great dry sense of humour. Granted, sometimes at 9 in the morning it's hard to remain engaged by her lectures, most of the time I was very interested.
Easiest course ever!

I agree that she is not very friendly. Assignments aren't very straightforward, but if you're naturally good at English, you can do quite well with her. She's very intelligent, although obviously favours certain students above others, which isn't fair in class discussions.
Worst prof I've ever had. Not friendly. If you sit at the back you cannot hear her. She speaks VERY VERY softly. Spare yourself, don't take this class.

I can't believe this woman got any good reviews. I HATED her class in 2000. Possibly the WORST teacher ever. A fill in the blanks poetry test for 35% in a second year class. WTF? Pure laziness on her part. The only good thing in that class was the TAs. Steer cleer of her. She should've ret'd by now.
Best prof ever.........so brilliant. Best prof I ever had, and made me want to take more courses in poetry. Take this class!
I liked her in the beginning, but towards the end she had a somewhat pretentious attitude about her & I felt intimidated to ask Qs. She is brilliant though.
Boring lectures and zero personality.  If you come to class, bring a pillow.

I don't think she liked me personally very much.. but I have a high respect for her & she is still my favourite prof. at U of T. Take her classes & be prepared to work hard (she doesn't like slackers ;)

The best professor of poetry I've had so far. It's a shame that I'm graduating and wish I could have taken many more classes with her. Prof. Reibetanz embodies the spirit of poetry - if you love poetry you will love her class.

Prof. Reibetanz is an amazing prof - my favourite thus far. She is a very intelligent person & has such a warm & caring personality; I never felt intimidated to ask questions or approach her in office hrs. I'm definitely taking another class with her.

I enjoyed this class and learned a great deal from it.  The professor was passionate about the subject which helped raise my own interest level in poetry.  The only downside was that she was very specifc about what she wanted in the essays.
Horrible, mean-spirited, close-minded person! Do yourself a favor, and steer clear!!!
